  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A comprehensive uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted across all five flow-speed operating points; parameter sweeps and Latin hypercube sampling were used to bound hemolysis predictions. UQ findings are summarised in the validation narrative and decision record.",
