    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scope per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. The UQ campaign (200-sample LHS over blood rheology parameters plus parametric geometry sweeps) demonstrated that RHI predictions are robust to input uncertainty, with variance below 8%. The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied at all five operating points with margin. The credibility evidence package supports regulatory submission for the Class II CPB device hemolysis assessment.",
